<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{{ report.ticker }} — Forensic Research Note · Muddy Reporter</title>

    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Source+Serif+4:opsz,wght@8..60,400;8..60,500;8..60,600;8..60,700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />

    <style>
      /* =================================================================
         INVESTMENT-BANK RESEARCH NOTE TEMPLATE
         - Page 1 = self-contained cover (rating box + summary + bottom line)
         - Page 2+ = body, each major section = numbered "Exhibit"
         - Print A4 with running header/footer + page numbers
         ================================================================= */

      @page {
        size: A4 portrait;
        margin: 20mm 16mm 24mm;
      }
      @page :first {
        margin: 16mm 16mm 22mm;
      }

      :root {
        --paper:        #ffffff;
        --paper-deep:   #f4f5f7;
        --paper-tint:   #f8f9fb;
        --paper-warm:   #faf7f0;   /* gold-tinted callout bg */
        --ink:          #0a1f44;
        --ink-body:     #1f2937;
        --ink-muted:    #6b7280;
        --ink-dim:      #9ca3af;
        --line:         #e1e4e9;
        --line-strong:  #cbd5e1;
        --navy:         #0a1f44;
        --navy-deep:    #061633;
        --gold:         #b29869;
        --gold-deep:    #9a8155;
        --gold-soft:    #d4c2a0;
        --good:         #065f46;
        --good-bg:      #f0fdf4;
        --good-line:    #bbf7d0;
        --warn:         #a16207;
        --warn-bg:      #fefce8;
        --warn-line:    #fde68a;
        --bad:          #9b1c1c;
        --bad-bg:       #fef2f2;
        --bad-line:     #fecaca;
        --info:         #1e40af;
        --info-bg:      #eff6ff;
        --info-line:    #bfdbfe;
      }

      * { box-sizing: border-box; }
      html, body {
        margin: 0; background: var(--paper); color: var(--ink-body);
        font-family: Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial;
        font-size: 11.5px; line-height: 1.55;
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      }
      a { color: var(--navy); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-strong); }
      a:hover { color: var(--navy-deep); border-bottom-color: var(--gold); }

      .doc {
        max-width: 1080px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 36px 60px;
      }

      /* =================================================================
         PRIMITIVES
         ================================================================= */
      .mono { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }
      .serif { font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; }
      .muted { color: var(--ink-muted); }
      .small { font-size: 10.5px; }
      .gold-rule {
        height: 1px;
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--gold) 18%, var(--gold) 82%, transparent);
      }
      .navy-rule { height: 2px; background: var(--navy); }
      .double-rule {
        height: 4px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--navy);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--navy);
      }

      /* =================================================================
         RUNNING HEADER (top of every page)
         ================================================================= */
      .running-header {
        padding: 8px 0 6px;
        display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 9.5px; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-muted);
      }
      .running-header .brand {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-weight: 700;
        font-size: 13px; color: var(--navy); letter-spacing: 0;
      }
      .running-header .brand .accent { color: var(--gold); margin: 0 6px; }
      .running-header .right { display: flex; gap: 14px; }
      .running-header .right .v { color: var(--ink-body); }

      .toolbar {
        display: flex; justify-content: flex-end; gap: 8px;
        margin: 8px 0 4px;
      }
      .btn {
        background: var(--navy); color: #fff; border: 0;
        padding: 6px 12px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase;
        cursor: pointer; font-weight: 500;
      }
      .btn:hover { background: var(--navy-deep); }
      .btn.ghost { background: #fff; color: var(--navy); border: 1px solid var(--line-strong); }
      .btn.ghost:hover { background: var(--paper-deep); }

      /* =================================================================
         PAGE 1 — COVER
         ================================================================= */
      .cover-page {
        page-break-after: always;
        min-height: calc(100vh - 100px);
        padding: 8px 0 28px;
      }

      .cover-eyebrow {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 10.5px; letter-spacing: 0.34em;
        text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--gold-deep);
        font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 18px;
        position: relative; padding-left: 28px;
      }
      .cover-eyebrow::before {
        content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 50%;
        width: 22px; height: 1px; background: var(--gold);
      }

      /* Two-col cover layout: name on left, rating box pinned right */
      .cover-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) 280px;
        gap: 36px;
        align-items: start;
      }

      .cover-name {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-weight: 700;
        font-size: 56px; line-height: 1.0;
        color: var(--navy); letter-spacing: -0.025em;
        margin: 0 0 6px;
      }
      .cover-ticker {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--gold-deep); margin-bottom: 16px;
      }
      .cover-tagline {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-style: italic;
        font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--ink-body);
        margin: 0 0 18px; max-width: 95%;
      }

      .at-a-glance {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        column-gap: 24px; row-gap: 6px;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10.5px;
        padding: 14px 0; margin: 16px 0 0;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
      }
      .at-a-glance .k {
        color: var(--ink-muted); text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.18em; font-size: 9px; font-weight: 600;
      }
      .at-a-glance .v { color: var(--ink-body); }

      /* RATING BOX — like a real research-note recommendation card */
      .rating-box {
        border: 1.5px solid var(--navy);
        background: #fff;
        padding: 0; overflow: hidden;
      }
      .rating-box .rating-head {
        background: var(--navy); color: #fff;
        padding: 10px 14px;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.22em;
        font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase;
        display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
      }
      .rating-box .rating-head .gold-mark { color: var(--gold); }
      .rating-section {
        padding: 14px 16px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
      }
      .rating-section:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
      .rating-section .lab {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-muted); margin-bottom: 4px;
      }

      .grade-display {
        display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 14px;
      }
      .grade-letter {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-weight: 700;
        font-size: 64px; line-height: 0.85; letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      }
      .grade-A { color: var(--good); }
      .grade-B { color: #4d7c0f; }
      .grade-C { color: var(--warn); }
      .grade-D { color: #b45309; }
      .grade-F { color: var(--bad); }
      .grade-meta {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 10.5px; line-height: 1.4;
      }
      .grade-meta .num { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--navy); }

      .ml-display .num {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-weight: 700;
        font-size: 42px; line-height: 0.9; letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        color: var(--navy);
      }
      .ml-display .num.bad { color: var(--bad); }
      .ml-display .num.warn { color: var(--warn); }
      .ml-display .num.good { color: var(--good); }
      .ml-display .verdict-row {
        display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; flex-wrap: wrap;
        margin-top: 6px;
      }

      .rating-stat-row {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 10.5px;
        gap: 8px; row-gap: 5px;
      }
      .rating-stat-row .k { color: var(--ink-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; font-size: 9px; }
      .rating-stat-row .v { color: var(--navy); font-weight: 600; text-align: right; }
      .rating-stat-row .v.bad { color: var(--bad); }
      .rating-stat-row .v.warn { color: var(--warn); }
      .rating-stat-row .v.good { color: var(--good); }

      /* Investment summary bullets */
      .inv-summary {
        margin-top: 28px;
      }
      .inv-summary .head {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 10.5px; letter-spacing: 0.24em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--navy); padding-bottom: 6px;
        border-bottom: 2px solid var(--navy); margin-bottom: 10px;
        display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 8px;
      }
      .inv-summary .head .gold-mark { color: var(--gold); }
      .inv-summary ul {
        list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0;
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.55;
        color: var(--ink-body);
      }
      .inv-summary li {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 22px 1fr;
        gap: 8px; padding: 6px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--line);
      }
      .inv-summary li:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
      .inv-summary .num {
        color: var(--gold-deep); font-weight: 700; font-style: italic;
      }
      .inv-summary li strong { color: var(--navy); }

      /* Bottom line callout */
      .bottom-line {
        margin: 24px 0 0;
        border-left: 4px solid var(--gold);
        background: var(--paper-warm);
        padding: 16px 22px;
      }
      .bottom-line .lab {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 9.5px; letter-spacing: 0.24em;
        color: var(--gold-deep); text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
      }
      .bottom-line .body {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif;
        font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--ink-body);
      }

      /* Footer of cover page */
      .cover-footer {
        margin-top: 28px; padding-top: 12px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
        display: flex; justify-content: space-between; gap: 16px;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-dim);
      }

      /* =================================================================
         PAGE 2+ — BODY SECTIONS as "EXHIBITS"
         ================================================================= */
      .body-page {
        padding-top: 12px;
      }

      .exhibit {
        margin-top: 28px;
        page-break-inside: auto;
      }
      .exhibit:first-child { margin-top: 14px; }

      .exhibit-head {
        margin-bottom: 14px;
        page-break-after: avoid;
      }
      .exhibit-eyebrow {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 9.5px; letter-spacing: 0.30em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold-deep); margin-bottom: 4px;
      }
      .exhibit-title {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; color: var(--navy);
        font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.018em;
        margin: 0 0 4px; line-height: 1.15;
      }
      .exhibit-sub {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-style: italic;
        color: var(--ink-muted); font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.45;
        margin: 0;
      }
      .exhibit-rule {
        border: 0;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--navy);
        margin: 6px 0 14px;
      }

      /* Generic prose */
      .prose { font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--ink-body); }
      .prose strong { color: var(--navy); }
      .prose ol, .prose ul { padding-left: 18px; margin: 6px 0 0; }
      .prose li { margin-bottom: 5px; }

      .prose-serif {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif;
        font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--ink-body);
      }
      .prose-serif strong { color: var(--navy); }

      /* Drop cap on the very first paragraph of the thesis */
      .drop-cap::first-letter {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--navy);
        font-size: 56px; line-height: 0.9;
        float: left; padding: 4px 8px 0 0;
      }

      /* Pull-quote — for one strong sentence, like a magazine */
      .pullquote {
        margin: 18px 0;
        padding: 10px 0 10px 24px;
        border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-style: italic;
        font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.4; color: var(--navy);
        max-width: 92%;
      }
      .pullquote .attrib {
        display: block; margin-top: 6px;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-style: normal;
        font-size: 9.5px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-muted);
      }

      /* Pills */
      .pill {
        display: inline-block; padding: 2px 7px;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.10em; font-weight: 500;
        border: 1px solid var(--line-strong); color: var(--ink-muted);
        background: var(--paper-deep);
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }
      .pill.fact, .pill.high { color: var(--bad); border-color: var(--bad-line); background: var(--bad-bg); }
      .pill.inference, .pill.medium { color: var(--info); border-color: var(--info-line); background: var(--info-bg); }
      .pill.question, .pill.low { color: var(--warn); border-color: var(--warn-line); background: var(--warn-bg); }
      .pill.speculation, .pill.suspicious, .pill.likely_fraud, .pill.likely_misrepresentation {
        color: var(--bad); border-color: var(--bad-line); background: var(--bad-bg);
      }
      .pill.clean { color: var(--good); border-color: var(--good-line); background: var(--good-bg); }
      .pill.watch { color: var(--warn); border-color: var(--warn-line); background: var(--warn-bg); }
      .pill.agree { color: var(--good); border-color: var(--good-line); background: var(--good-bg); }
      .pill.disagree { color: var(--warn); border-color: var(--warn-line); background: var(--warn-bg); }

      /* =================================================================
         FINDING — research-note style numbered entry
         ================================================================= */
      .finding {
        padding: 16px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
        page-break-inside: avoid;
      }
      .finding:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
      .finding-head {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 50px 1fr;
        gap: 12px; align-items: baseline;
      }
      .finding .num {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--gold-deep); font-size: 28px; line-height: 1;
        letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      }
      .finding .num small {
        display: block; font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.2em;
        color: var(--ink-muted); text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-top: 4px; font-weight: 500;
      }
      .finding h4 {
        margin: 0; font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--navy); font-size: 16px; letter-spacing: -0.012em;
        line-height: 1.25;
      }
      .finding .pills { margin: 6px 0 8px 62px; }
      .finding .body { margin-left: 62px; }
      .finding .why {
        border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
        background: var(--paper-warm); padding: 8px 14px; margin: 10px 0;
      }
      .finding .why .lab {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 8.5px; letter-spacing: 0.22em;
        color: var(--gold-deep); text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      .quote {
        white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 10.5px; color: var(--ink-body); line-height: 1.55;
        background: var(--paper-deep);
        border-left: 3px solid var(--navy);
        padding: 8px 12px; margin: 4px 0;
      }
      .cite {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px;
        word-break: break-all;
      }
      .subhead {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-muted); margin: 12px 0 4px;
      }

      /* =================================================================
         FORENSIC SCORE TILES — uniform 3-up
         ================================================================= */
      .score-row {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 10px;
      }
      .score-tile {
        border: 1px solid var(--line); padding: 14px 16px;
        position: relative; background: #fff; page-break-inside: avoid;
      }
      .score-tile::before {
        content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0; bottom: 0;
        width: 3px; background: var(--navy);
      }
      .score-tile .lab {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 9.5px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-muted);
      }
      .score-tile .num {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-weight: 700;
        font-size: 32px; line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        margin: 8px 0; color: var(--navy);
      }
      .score-tile .num.bad { color: var(--bad); }
      .score-tile .num.warn { color: var(--warn); }
      .score-tile .num.good { color: var(--good); }
      .score-tile .note { font-size: 10px; color: var(--ink-muted); line-height: 1.5; }

      /* =================================================================
         TABLES
         ================================================================= */
      table.tabular {
        width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10.5px;
      }
      table.tabular th {
        background: var(--paper-tint); color: var(--ink-muted);
        font-weight: 600; font-size: 9px;
        letter-spacing: 0.20em; text-transform: uppercase;
        text-align: right; padding: 8px 12px;
        border-bottom: 2px solid var(--navy);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
      }
      table.tabular th:first-child { text-align: left; }
      table.tabular td {
        padding: 8px 12px; text-align: right;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
      }
      table.tabular td:first-child { text-align: left; color: var(--navy); font-weight: 500; }
      table.tabular tbody tr:hover { background: var(--paper-tint); }

      table.ev-ledger {
        width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 10.5px;
      }
      table.ev-ledger th {
        background: var(--navy); color: #fff;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase;
        text-align: left; padding: 9px 12px;
      }
      table.ev-ledger td {
        padding: 12px; vertical-align: top;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
      }
      table.ev-ledger tbody tr { page-break-inside: avoid; }
      table.ev-ledger tbody tr:nth-child(even) { background: var(--paper-tint); }

      .anomaly {
        border: 1px solid var(--line); padding: 14px 16px; margin-bottom: 10px;
        position: relative; background: #fff; page-break-inside: avoid;
      }
      .anomaly::before {
        content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0; bottom: 0;
        width: 3px; background: var(--gold);
      }
      .anomaly h4 {
        margin: 0 0 4px; font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif;
        color: var(--navy); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600;
      }

      .claim-row {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        border: 1px solid var(--line); margin-bottom: 10px;
        page-break-inside: avoid; background: #fff;
      }
      .claim-row > div { padding: 14px 16px; }
      .claim-row > div:first-child {
        border-right: 1px solid var(--line); background: var(--paper-deep);
      }
      .claim-row .role {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 8.5px;
        letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-muted); margin-bottom: 6px;
      }
      .claim-row .role.counter { color: var(--bad); }

      .cat-grid {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 12px;
      }
      .cat-card {
        border: 1px solid var(--line); padding: 12px 14px; background: #fff;
        page-break-inside: avoid;
      }
      .cat-card .lab {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold-deep); margin-bottom: 6px;
      }
      .cat-card ul { padding-left: 16px; margin: 0; font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.6; }

      /* =================================================================
         SOURCES / DISCLAIMER
         ================================================================= */
      .sources {
        margin-top: 18px;
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 16px;
      }
      .source-card {
        border: 1px solid var(--line); padding: 12px 14px;
        position: relative; background: #fff;
      }
      .source-card::before {
        content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0; bottom: 0;
        width: 3px; background: var(--navy);
      }
      .source-card .top {
        display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between;
        margin-bottom: 4px;
      }
      .source-card .ftype {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--navy); font-size: 14px;
      }
      .source-card .fdate {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px;
        color: var(--ink-muted);
      }

      .disclaimer {
        margin-top: 36px; padding-top: 18px;
        border-top: 2px solid var(--navy);
        font-size: 9.5px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--ink-muted);
        page-break-inside: avoid;
      }
      .disclaimer h5 {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.24em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--navy); margin: 0 0 8px;
      }
      .disclaimer p { margin: 0 0 8px; }
      .disclaimer .signoff {
        margin-top: 14px; padding-top: 10px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
        display: flex; justify-content: space-between; gap: 16px;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px;
        letter-spacing: 0.10em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-dim);
      }

      /* =================================================================
         PRINT
         ================================================================= */
      @media print {
        body { font-size: 10.5px; }
        .toolbar, .no-print { display: none !important; }
        .doc { padding: 0; max-width: none; }
        .cover-page { min-height: 0; }
        a { color: var(--navy); border: 0; }
        @page {
          @bottom-left {
            content: "Muddy Reporter · Forensic Equity Research · {{ report.ticker }}";
            font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
            font-size: 7.5pt; color: #6b7280;
            letter-spacing: 0.10em;
          }
          @bottom-right {
            content: "Page " counter(page) " of " counter(pages);
            font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
            font-size: 7.5pt; color: #6b7280;
          }
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="doc">

      <!-- ================================================================
           RUNNING HEADER (every page; print uses @page rules to repeat)
           ================================================================ -->
      <header class="running-header">
        <span class="brand">Muddy Reporter <span class="accent">|</span> Forensic Equity Research</span>
        <span class="right">
          <span>{{ report.ticker }}</span>
          <span class="v">{{ report.generated_at_iso[:10] if report.generated_at_iso else '' }}</span>
        </span>
      </header>
      <div class="gold-rule"></div>

      <div class="toolbar no-print">
        <button class="btn ghost" onclick="window.print()">Print / save PDF</button>
      </div>

      <!-- ================================================================
           PAGE 1 — COVER
           ================================================================ -->
      <section class="cover-page">

        <div class="cover-eyebrow">Research Note &nbsp;·&nbsp; Concern thesis</div>

        <div class="cover-grid">

          <!-- Left side: company name + tagline + at-a-glance -->
          <div>
            <h1 class="cover-name">{{ report.company_name or report.ticker }}</h1>
            <div class="cover-ticker">{{ report.ticker }}</div>

            {% if report.snapshot.business_description %}
            <p class="cover-tagline">{{ report.snapshot.business_description }}</p>
            {% endif %}

            <div class="at-a-glance">
              <div class="k">Sources analyzed</div>
              <div class="v">{{ sources | length }} SEC filings + XBRL</div>

              {% set ftypes = sources|map(attribute='filing_type')|list|unique|list %}
              <div class="k">Filing types</div>
              <div class="v">{{ ftypes|join(', ') if ftypes else '—' }}</div>

              <div class="k">LLM engine</div>
              <div class="v">{{ report.provider_info.provider if report.provider_info else 'n/a' }} · {{ report.provider_info.model if report.provider_info else 'n/a' }}</div>

              <div class="k">Issued</div>
              <div class="v">{{ report.generated_at_iso }}</div>

              {% if report.snapshot.where_it_operates %}
              <div class="k">Geography</div>
              <div class="v">{{ report.snapshot.where_it_operates[:80] }}{% if report.snapshot.where_it_operates|length > 80 %}…{% endif %}</div>
              {% endif %}

              <div class="k">Form factor</div>
              <div class="v">Forensic / skeptical, with verified citations</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Right side: rating box -->
          <aside class="rating-box">
            <div class="rating-head">
              Rating <span class="gold-mark">|</span> Risk
            </div>

            {% if report.risk_grade and report.risk_grade.grade %}
            <div class="rating-section">
              <div class="lab">Composite risk grade</div>
              <div class="grade-display">
                <span class="grade-letter grade-{{ report.risk_grade.grade }}">{{ report.risk_grade.grade }}</span>
                <div class="grade-meta">
                  <div class="num">{{ report.risk_grade.score }}<span class="muted" style="font-size:11px;">/100</span></div>
                  <div class="muted small" style="margin-top:4px;">Aggregated from XBRL anomalies, forensic scores, and LLM finding mix.</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            {% endif %}

            {% if report.fraud_ensemble %}
            <div class="rating-section ml-display">
              <div class="lab">Misrepresentation risk</div>
              <div class="num {% if (report.fraud_ensemble.combined_probability or 0) >= 0.7 %}bad{% elif (report.fraud_ensemble.combined_probability or 0) >= 0.45 %}warn{% else %}good{% endif %}">{{ "%.0f"|format((report.fraud_ensemble.combined_probability or 0) * 100) }}%</div>
              <div class="verdict-row">
                <span class="pill {{ report.fraud_ensemble.verdict|replace('likely_misrepresentation','likely_fraud') }}">{{ (report.fraud_ensemble.verdict or 'watch')|replace('_',' ') }}</span>
                {% if report.fraud_ensemble.agreement %}<span class="pill {{ report.fraud_ensemble.agreement }}">models {{ report.fraud_ensemble.agreement }}</span>{% endif %}
              </div>
              <div class="muted small" style="margin-top:6px;">Two-model ensemble: LLM few-shot + deterministic logistic regression.</div>
            </div>
            {% endif %}

            <div class="rating-section">
              <div class="lab">Extracted</div>
              <div class="rating-stat-row">
                <div class="k">Red flags</div><div class="v {% if (report.red_flags|length) >= 5 %}bad{% elif (report.red_flags|length) >= 1 %}warn{% endif %}">{{ report.red_flags | length }}</div>
                <div class="k">Quant anomalies</div><div class="v {% if (report.financial_anomalies|length) >= 3 %}bad{% elif (report.financial_anomalies|length) >= 1 %}warn{% endif %}">{{ report.financial_anomalies | length }}</div>
                <div class="k">Mgmt claims tested</div><div class="v">{{ report.management_claims_vs_counterpoints | length }}</div>
                <div class="k">Open questions</div><div class="v">{{ report.open_questions | length }}</div>
                <div class="k">Evidence rows</div><div class="v">{{ report.evidence_summary | length }}</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            {% if report.forensic_scores %}
            <div class="rating-section">
              <div class="lab">Forensic models</div>
              <div class="rating-stat-row">
                {% if report.forensic_scores.beneish_m is not none %}
                <div class="k">Beneish M</div><div class="v {% if report.forensic_scores.beneish_signal == 'manipulator' %}bad{% else %}good{% endif %}">{{ report.forensic_scores.beneish_m }}</div>
                {% endif %}
                {% if report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f is not none %}
                <div class="k">Piotroski F</div><div class="v {% if report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f >= 7 %}good{% elif report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f <= 3 %}bad{% else %}warn{% endif %}">{{ report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f }}/9</div>
                {% endif %}
                {% if report.forensic_scores.altman_z is not none %}
                <div class="k">Altman Z'</div><div class="v {% if report.forensic_scores.altman_zone == 'distress' %}bad{% elif report.forensic_scores.altman_zone == 'safe' %}good{% else %}warn{% endif %}">{{ report.forensic_scores.altman_z }}</div>
                {% endif %}
              </div>
            </div>
            {% endif %}
          </aside>

        </div>

        <!-- INVESTMENT SUMMARY — top concerns as analyst bullets -->
        {% if report.red_flags %}
        <div class="inv-summary">
          <div class="head">Investment summary <span class="gold-mark">|</span> top concerns</div>
          <ul>
            {% for f in report.red_flags[:5] %}
            <li>
              <span class="num">{{ "%02d"|format(loop.index) }}</span>
              <span><strong>{{ f.title }}.</strong> {{ (f.claim_or_observation or '')[:200] }}{% if (f.claim_or_observation or '')|length > 200 %}…{% endif %}</span>
            </li>
            {% endfor %}
          </ul>
        </div>
        {% endif %}

        <!-- BOTTOM LINE — analyst TL;DR -->
        <div class="bottom-line">
          <div class="lab">Bottom line</div>
          <div class="body">{{ report.core_thesis or 'No thesis extracted.' }}</div>
        </div>

        <div class="cover-footer">
          <span>© Muddy Reporter Prototype · Case-study build</span>
          <span>Page 1 of report · {{ report.ticker }}</span>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ================================================================
           PAGE 2+ — BODY (each section labeled "Exhibit N")
           ================================================================ -->
      <section class="body-page">

        {# ====== Exhibit 1: Snapshot & thesis ====== #}
        <div class="exhibit">
          <div class="exhibit-head">
            <div class="exhibit-eyebrow">Exhibit 01 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Concern thesis</div>
            <h2 class="exhibit-title">Why this name merits scrutiny</h2>
            <p class="exhibit-sub">A skeptical, investigative framing built from public SEC filings — not an allegation of wrongdoing, not a recommendation to act.</p>
            <hr class="exhibit-rule"/>
          </div>

          <div class="prose-serif drop-cap">{{ report.core_thesis or '—' }}</div>

          {# Pull-quote: highlight the strongest fact-labeled finding #}
          {% set top_fact = (report.red_flags or []) | selectattr('label', 'equalto', 'fact') | list %}
          {% if top_fact %}
          {% set tf = top_fact[0] %}
          <div class="pullquote">
            “{{ tf.title }} — {{ (tf.claim_or_observation or '')[:240] }}”
            <span class="attrib">Lead finding · cited in {{ tf.citations[0].doc_id if tf.citations else 'filing' }}</span>
          </div>
          {% endif %}

          <div class="prose" style="margin-top:14px;">
            <p><strong>What we did.</strong> Pulled <strong>{{ sources|length }} SEC filings</strong> ({{ ftypes|join(', ') if ftypes else 'mixed' }}), parsed the full XBRL company-facts feed, ran deterministic anomaly detection, computed three academic forensic scores (Beneish, Piotroski, Altman Z'), then asked an LLM ({{ report.provider_info.model if report.provider_info else 'n/a' }}) to extract red flags chunk-by-chunk under a strict label/confidence/citation schema. A second deterministic logistic-regression scorer was run in parallel and the two were ensembled.</p>

            {% if report.snapshot.where_it_operates %}<p><strong>Where it operates.</strong> {{ report.snapshot.where_it_operates }}</p>{% endif %}
            {% if report.snapshot.segments_or_revenue_model %}<p><strong>Revenue model / segments.</strong> {{ report.snapshot.segments_or_revenue_model }}</p>{% endif %}
            {% if report.snapshot.recent_corporate_actions %}<p><strong>Recent corporate actions.</strong> {{ report.snapshot.recent_corporate_actions }}</p>{% endif %}
          </div>
        </div>

        {# ====== Exhibit 2: Forensic models ====== #}
        {% if report.forensic_scores and (report.forensic_scores.beneish_m is not none or report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f is not none or report.forensic_scores.altman_z is not none) %}
        <div class="exhibit">
          <div class="exhibit-head">
            <div class="exhibit-eyebrow">Exhibit 02 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Quantitative forensic models</div>
            <h2 class="exhibit-title">Beneish &middot; Piotroski &middot; Altman</h2>
            <p class="exhibit-sub">Three peer-reviewed academic models, computed deterministically from the issuer's filed XBRL. Numbers are reproducible from the source data.</p>
            <hr class="exhibit-rule"/>
          </div>
          <div class="score-row">
            {% if report.forensic_scores.beneish_m is not none %}
            <div class="score-tile">
              <div class="lab">Beneish M-Score</div>
              <div class="num {% if report.forensic_scores.beneish_signal == 'manipulator' %}bad{% else %}good{% endif %}">{{ report.forensic_scores.beneish_m }}</div>
              <div class="note"><strong>Threshold:</strong> M &gt; -1.78 = likely earnings manipulator (Beneish 1999). Combines 8 ratio components covering revenue quality, asset quality, leverage, and accruals.</div>
            </div>
            {% endif %}
            {% if report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f is not none %}
            <div class="score-tile">
              <div class="lab">Piotroski F-Score</div>
              <div class="num {% if report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f >= 7 %}good{% elif report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f <= 3 %}bad{% else %}warn{% endif %}">{{ report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f }}<span class="muted" style="font-size:14px;">/9</span></div>
              <div class="note"><strong>Threshold:</strong> F &le; 3 = financially weak; F &ge; 7 = strong (Piotroski 2000). Nine binary tests of profitability, leverage and operating efficiency.</div>
            </div>
            {% endif %}
            {% if report.forensic_scores.altman_z is not none %}
            <div class="score-tile">
              <div class="lab">Altman Z'-Score</div>
              <div class="num {% if report.forensic_scores.altman_zone == 'distress' %}bad{% elif report.forensic_scores.altman_zone == 'safe' %}good{% else %}warn{% endif %}">{{ report.forensic_scores.altman_z }}</div>
              <div class="note"><strong>Zone:</strong> {{ report.forensic_scores.altman_zone or 'gray' }}. Bankruptcy probability over 1-2 years. Z' &lt; 1.23 = distress, Z' &gt; 2.90 = safe (Altman 1983 private-firm variant).</div>
            </div>
            {% endif %}
          </div>
        </div>
        {% endif %}

        {# ====== Exhibit 3: XBRL anomalies ====== #}
        {% if report.financial_anomalies %}
        <div class="exhibit">
          <div class="exhibit-head">
            <div class="exhibit-eyebrow">Exhibit 03 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Pattern-based XBRL anomalies</div>
            <h2 class="exhibit-title">Quantitative red flags from the filings</h2>
            <p class="exhibit-sub">Rule-based pattern checks against the issuer's filed XBRL data. No LLM in this layer — every signal is reproducible from the SEC company-facts API.</p>
            <hr class="exhibit-rule"/>
          </div>
          {% for a in report.financial_anomalies %}
          <div class="anomaly">
            <h4>{{ a.title }}</h4>
            <div style="margin: 4px 0 6px;">
              <span class="pill {{ a.severity }}">{{ a.severity }}</span>
              <span class="pill">{{ a.category }}</span>
              <span class="pill">{{ a.metric }}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="prose small">{{ a.description }}</div>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
        {% endif %}

        {# ====== Exhibit 4: Top red flags ====== #}
        <div class="exhibit">
          <div class="exhibit-head">
            <div class="exhibit-eyebrow">Exhibit 04 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Top red flags</div>
            <h2 class="exhibit-title">Skeptical findings extracted from filings</h2>
            <p class="exhibit-sub">Each finding tagged with its label (fact / inference / question / speculation), confidence, and a verbatim citation. Independent verification against the cited filing is required.</p>
            <hr class="exhibit-rule"/>
          </div>
          {% for f in report.red_flags %}
          <div class="finding">
            <div class="finding-head">
              <span class="num">{{ "%02d"|format(loop.index) }}<small>finding</small></span>
              <h4>{{ f.title }}</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="pills">
              <span class="pill {{ f.label }}">{{ f.label }}</span>
              <span class="pill {{ f.confidence }}">conf {{ f.confidence }}</span>
              <span class="pill">{{ f.category|replace('_',' ') }}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="body prose">
              <p><strong>Observation.</strong> {{ f.claim_or_observation }}</p>
              <div class="why">
                <div class="lab">Why it matters</div>
                <div style="margin-top:3px;">{{ f.why_it_matters }}</div>
              </div>

              {% if f.counterpoints_or_alt_explanations %}
              <div class="subhead">Counterpoints / alt. explanations</div>
              <ul>{% for c in f.counterpoints_or_alt_explanations %}<li>{{ c }}</li>{% endfor %}</ul>
              {% endif %}

              {% if f.open_questions %}
              <div class="subhead">Open questions</div>
              <ul>{% for q in f.open_questions %}<li>{{ q }}</li>{% endfor %}</ul>
              {% endif %}

              {% if f.citations %}
              <div class="subhead">Cited evidence</div>
              {% for ci in f.citations %}
              <div style="margin-bottom:8px;">
                <a class="cite" href="{{ ci.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">{{ ci.doc_id }}</a>
                <div class="quote">{{ ci.excerpt }}</div>
              </div>
              {% endfor %}
              {% else %}
              <div class="small muted" style="margin-top:6px;">No direct citation captured — treat as low-confidence pending verification.</div>
              {% endif %}
            </div>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>

        {# ====== Exhibit 5: Evidence ledger ====== #}
        {% if report.evidence_summary %}
        <div class="exhibit">
          <div class="exhibit-head">
            <div class="exhibit-eyebrow">Exhibit 05 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Evidence ledger</div>
            <h2 class="exhibit-title">Per-citation table tied to source documents</h2>
            <p class="exhibit-sub">One row per cited excerpt. Sorted by evidence strength: facts, then inferences, then questions, then speculation.</p>
            <hr class="exhibit-rule"/>
          </div>
          <table class="ev-ledger">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th style="width:7%;">Label</th>
                <th style="width:32%;">Finding</th>
                <th style="width:18%;">Source filing</th>
                <th>Cited excerpt</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              {% for r in report.evidence_summary %}
              <tr>
                <td>
                  <span class="pill {{ r.label }}">{{ r.label }}</span>
                  <div class="small muted" style="margin-top:3px;">{{ r.confidence }}</div>
                </td>
                <td>
                  <div style="font-weight:600;color:var(--navy);font-size:11px;">{{ r.finding_title }}</div>
                  {% if r.category %}<div class="small muted mono" style="margin-top:3px;">{{ r.category|replace('_',' ') }}</div>{% endif %}
                  {% if r.why_it_matters %}<div class="small" style="margin-top:4px;">{{ r.why_it_matters }}</div>{% endif %}
                </td>
                <td class="cite">
                  {% if r.url %}
                  <a href="{{ r.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">{{ r.filing_type or 'filing' }} · {{ r.filing_date or '' }}</a>
                  {% elif r.missing_citation %}
                  <span class="muted small">— no source cited —</span>
                  {% else %}
                  <span class="muted small">{{ r.filing_type or 'unknown' }}</span>
                  {% endif %}
                </td>
                <td>
                  {% if r.excerpt %}<div class="quote" style="margin:0;">{{ r.excerpt }}</div>
                  {% else %}<span class="muted small">No excerpt captured</span>{% endif %}
                </td>
              </tr>
              {% endfor %}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        {% endif %}

        {# ====== Exhibit 6: Management claims vs counterpoints ====== #}
        {% if report.management_claims_vs_counterpoints %}
        <div class="exhibit">
          <div class="exhibit-head">
            <div class="exhibit-eyebrow">Exhibit 06 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Management vs filings</div>
            <h2 class="exhibit-title">Claims tested against the disclosure</h2>
            <p class="exhibit-sub">Each row pairs a management statement with a skeptical counterpoint or inconsistency surfaced from the same source documents.</p>
            <hr class="exhibit-rule"/>
          </div>
          {% for row in report.management_claims_vs_counterpoints %}
          <div class="claim-row">
            <div>
              <div class="role">Management</div>
              <div class="prose small">{{ row.claim }}</div>
              {% if row.source_excerpt %}<div class="quote" style="margin-top:8px;">{{ row.source_excerpt }}</div>{% endif %}
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="role counter">Counterpoint / inconsistency</div>
              <div class="prose small">{{ row.counterpoint }}</div>
              <div style="margin-top:6px;">
                <span class="pill {{ row.confidence }}">conf {{ row.confidence }}</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
        {% endif %}

        {# ====== Exhibit 7: Concerns by category ====== #}
        {% if report.concerns_by_category %}
        <div class="exhibit">
          <div class="exhibit-head">
            <div class="exhibit-eyebrow">Exhibit 07 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Issue map</div>
            <h2 class="exhibit-title">Concerns by category</h2>
            <p class="exhibit-sub">Accounting · Governance · Disclosure · Operations — categorized for diligence routing.</p>
            <hr class="exhibit-rule"/>
          </div>
          <div class="cat-grid">
            {% for cat, items in report.concerns_by_category.items() %}
            <div class="cat-card">
              <div class="lab">{{ cat|replace('_',' ') }}</div>
              {% if items %}<ul>{% for it in items %}<li>{{ it }}</li>{% endfor %}</ul>
              {% else %}<div class="small muted">No specific concerns extracted.</div>{% endif %}
            </div>
            {% endfor %}
          </div>
        </div>
        {% endif %}

        {# ====== Exhibit 8: Open questions ====== #}
        <div class="exhibit">
          <div class="exhibit-head">
            <div class="exhibit-eyebrow">Exhibit 08 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Diligence agenda</div>
            <h2 class="exhibit-title">Questions for management</h2>
            <p class="exhibit-sub">Where independent diligence and IR follow-up should focus before drawing any conclusion.</p>
            <hr class="exhibit-rule"/>
          </div>
          {% if report.open_questions %}
          <ol class="prose">
            {% for q in report.open_questions %}<li>{{ q }}</li>{% endfor %}
          </ol>
          {% else %}
          <p class="prose muted">No questions extracted.</p>
          {% endif %}
        </div>

        {# ====== Exhibit 9: Annual financials ====== #}
        {% if report.financial_table %}
        <div class="exhibit">
          <div class="exhibit-head">
            <div class="exhibit-eyebrow">Exhibit 09 &nbsp;·&nbsp; XBRL · last seven fiscal years</div>
            <h2 class="exhibit-title">Annual financials</h2>
            <p class="exhibit-sub">Reporting-currency units as filed. Blanks indicate the concept was not tagged in that period (typical for foreign-private issuers and segment-level reporting).</p>
            <hr class="exhibit-rule"/>
          </div>
          <table class="tabular">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Year</th><th>Revenue</th><th>Net income</th><th>CFO</th>
                <th>AR</th><th>Inventory</th><th>Goodwill</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              {% macro fnum(v) -%}
                {% if v is none or v is undefined %}—{% else %}{{ "{:,.0f}".format(v) }}{% endif %}
              {%- endmacro %}
              {% for row in report.financial_table %}
              <tr>
                <td>{{ row.year }}</td>
                <td>{{ fnum(row.get('revenue')) }}</td>
                <td>{{ fnum(row.get('net_income')) }}</td>
                <td>{{ fnum(row.get('operating_cash_flow')) }}</td>
                <td>{{ fnum(row.get('accounts_receivable')) }}</td>
                <td>{{ fnum(row.get('inventory')) }}</td>
                <td>{{ fnum(row.get('goodwill')) }}</td>
              </tr>
              {% endfor %}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        {% endif %}

        {# ====== Exhibit 10: Conclusion ====== #}
        <div class="exhibit">
          <div class="exhibit-head">
            <div class="exhibit-eyebrow">Exhibit 10 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Caution framing</div>
            <h2 class="exhibit-title">Conclusion</h2>
            <hr class="exhibit-rule"/>
          </div>
          <div class="prose-serif">{{ report.conclusion or '—' }}</div>
        </div>

        {# ====== Exhibit 11: Sources ====== #}
        {% if sources %}
        <div class="exhibit">
          <div class="exhibit-head">
            <div class="exhibit-eyebrow">Exhibit 11 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Citations index</div>
            <h2 class="exhibit-title">Source filings analyzed</h2>
            <hr class="exhibit-rule"/>
          </div>
          <div class="sources">
            {% for s in sources %}
            <div class="source-card">
              <div class="top">
                <span class="ftype">{{ s.filing_type }}</span>
                <span class="fdate">{{ s.filing_date or 'undated' }}</span>
              </div>
              <a class="cite" href="{{ s.primary_url }}" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">{{ s.doc_id }}</a>
            </div>
            {% endfor %}
          </div>
        </div>
        {% endif %}

        <!-- ============================================================
             DISCLAIMER & METHODOLOGY
             ============================================================ -->
        <section class="disclaimer">
          <h5>Methodology &amp; limitations</h5>
          {% if report.limitations %}
          <ul style="padding-left:18px;margin:0 0 8px;">
            {% for l in report.limitations %}<li>{{ l }}</li>{% endfor %}
          </ul>
          {% endif %}
          <p>This document is a <strong style="color:var(--navy);">concern thesis</strong> generated by an automated forensic-research prototype, not investment advice and not an allegation of wrongdoing. Every claim is graded for confidence (fact / inference / question / speculation) and tied to a verbatim citation drawn from the issuer's public SEC filings. Independent verification against those filings is required before acting on any individual finding.</p>
          <p>The misrepresentation-risk percentage on the cover is the average of two independent estimators &mdash; an LLM few-shot classifier (DeepSeek V4 Pro / Gemini 2.5 / GPT-4.1) and a deterministic logistic-regression scorer trained on a curated set of historical fraud and control cases &mdash; weighted by each model's calibrated confidence and feature coverage. A <em>disagree</em> flag means the two models reached different verdicts; the combined number should then be treated with extra caution.</p>
          <p>Forensic models (Beneish 1999, Piotroski 2000, Altman 1983) are computed deterministically from the issuer's filed XBRL company-facts. Their thresholds are taken from the published academic literature; the same numbers apply equally to issuers we believe to be clean and to issuers we believe to be at risk. The score itself is a screening signal, not a verdict.</p>

          <div class="signoff">
            <span>© Muddy Reporter Prototype · Case-study build</span>
            <span>{{ report.ticker }} &nbsp;·&nbsp; generated {{ report.generated_at_iso }}</span>
          </div>
        </section>

      </section>

    </main>
